Roles & ResponsibilitiesJob Summary
Are you looking to work as a Data Scientist and expand your horizon while working on future-state projects? You will be part of the Cybersecurity arm that uses the data to discover and predict potential cyber incidents and threats before they even happened!

Mandatory Skill-set

Bachelors or Masters in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Statistics, Applied Mathematics, Data Science and Analytics;
At least 4 years of experience in quantitative data analytics or machine learning model development for cybersecurity using big data platforms;
Good hands on experience solving business problems using Data Analysis, Machine Learning, Predictive Modelling and other advanced statistical techniques;
Knowledge of a variety of machine learning techniques (clustering, decision tree learning, artificial neural networks, etc.);
Experienced in using databases and frameworks for big data analytics such as Hadoop/Hive/Spark;
Proficient in writing complex SQL queries;
Familiar with big data streaming and visualization tools such as Apache NiFi, Storm, Spark, Airflow, Kibana, Tableau;
Able to apply scientific thinking to solving business problems through analytics and data;
Must be willing to get involved with administrative work along with technical, research and development work;
Possess excellent written, verbal and presentation skills.

Desired Skill-set

Good understanding of Artificial Intelligence and Deep Learning concepts;
Domain knowledge and experience in Computer Networking/Network Security/System Security.

Responsibilities

Involved in conceptualizing, architecting and executing projects related to cybersecurity using big data and used cases;
Understand the organization needs and strategize data analytics development focus areas;
Research and implement new statistical or machine learning models, using mathematical methodologies as needed;
Mine and analyze data to drive optimization and improvements/customizations for current data analytics models;
Build predictive models to identify trends, develop insights and co-ordinate with teams to implement the models and monitor outcomes;
Create processes, tools or best practices in monitoring and analyzing the model performance and accuracy;
Work with different functional teams and get their buy-in on the model usages;
Liaise with vendors to data analytics stream development;
Work closely with senior stakeholders to identify opportunities in using data to improve cybersecurity capabilities;
Interpret technical statistical results and work towards improving the cybersecurity capabilities of the organization;
Monitor advancements in big data technologies and identify new tools to fine tune existing data analytics platform.

